Together we will investigate the emergence, flourishing and lasting appeal of non-conformist movements in Islamic intellectual history from the 10th century to the present day.

My own research on ‘Literary Qalandars’ will explore antinomian motifs, metaphors, imagery, and stories (which are meant to challenge the religious hierarchy and orthodox Islam) in Persian poetry from the 12th century onward.
